<subSubSection id="C300A1C27954FF98BEA67A0DC965FAC5" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA5F2497954FF98BEA67A0DC919FB79" blockId="13.[151,1436,1048,1500]" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B7954FF98BEA67A0DC968FBEC" bold="true" box="[151,280,1048,1074]" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Thorax, abdomen and legs predominantly yellow to yellow-reddish; postcranium black, shining black with no gray pruinescence on upper third; fore tarsomeres 1–3 not whitish distally; male tergite 8 with distal projection moderately truncated. Female hind tibia with pinnate scales along most of dorsal surface and ventral basal half.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA5F2497954FF98BEF47AA1C965FAC5" blockId="13.[151,1436,1048,1500]" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">
<materialsCitation id="3B72F8147954FF98BEF47AA1C960FAC5" collectionCode="AMNH" country="Panama" location="Canal Zone" municipality="Barro Colorado Island" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" specimenCount="2" typeStatus="holotype">
This species was redescribed and figured by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8B8FB87954FF98BCE87AA1CBF0FB10" author="Rafael" box="[729,896,1204,1230]" firstAuthor="Rafael" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" pagination="127 - 132" refId="ref9412" refString="Rafael, J. A. (2001). Redescricao de duas especies neotropicais de Empididae (Diptera) descritas por Curran e revalidacao do genero Porphyrochroa. Iheringia, Serie Zoologia, 90, 127 - 132." type="journal article" year="2001">Rafael (2001)</bibRefCitation>
. It is known only from a pair (
<typeStatus id="54A14CEB7954FF98BADB7AA1CD23FB10" box="[1258,1363,1204,1230]" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">holotype</typeStatus>
male, 
<typeStatus id="54A14CEB7954FF98BEA67ACFC885FB2A" box="[151,245,1242,1268]" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">allotype</typeStatus>
female) collected from 
<collectingCountry id="F30DB2D97954FF98BC3D7ACFCA19FB2A" box="[524,617,1242,1268]" name="Panama" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">Panama</collectingCountry>
(
<location id="8EC5A4927954FF98BC467ACFCB73FB2A" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03B3435F7954FF98BEA67CEBCAC2FA02:8EC5A4927954FF98BC467ACFCB73FB2A" box="[631,771,1242,1268]" country="Panama" municipality="Barro Colorado Island" name="Canal Zone" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">Canal Zone</location>
, 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BC168337954FF98BD3F7ACFCC64FB2A" box="[782,1044,1242,1268]" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">Barro Colorado Island</collectingMunicipality>
) (
<figureCitation id="1321EECC7954FF98BA1D7ACFCC02FB2A" box="[1068,1138,1242,1268]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,258,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[411,1210,1144,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-134@15.[355,1229,1144,1914]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. Distribution map of species belonging to the Macrostomus ferrugineus species-group with tergite 8 truncated or forked distally. Symbols represent the known collection localities as follows: diamond = M. longipennis, n. sp.; open circle = M. furcatus, n. sp.; open triangle = M. flavus, n. sp.; square = M. fulvithorax; star = M. occidentalis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321598" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321598/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
), in copula and deposited at 
<collectionCode id="ED0B6A8C7954FF98BE827B14C960FAC5" box="[179,272,1281,1307]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" name="American Museum of Natural History" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">AMNH</collectionCode>
</materialsCitation>
