<subSubSection id="C300A1C27954FF98BEF47B32CAC2FA02" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA5F2497954FF98BEF47B32CAC2FA02" blockId="13.[151,1436,1048,1500]" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B7954FF98BEF47B32C923FA9F" bold="true" box="[197,339,1319,1345]" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">Discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA7954FF98BF6D7B3DCAFAFA9F" box="[348,650,1320,1345]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvithorax">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B7954FF98BF6D7B3DCAFAFA9F" box="[348,650,1320,1345]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">Macrostomus fulvithorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has nearly the same shape of hypandrium as 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA7954FF98BA837B3DCD15FA9F" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1805" box="[1202,1381,1320,1345]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferrugineus">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B7954FF98BA837B3DCD15FA9F" box="[1202,1381,1320,1345]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">M. ferrugineus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but with no setae ventrally. It appears to be most closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA7954FF98BDA57B5ACC3DFAB6" box="[916,1101,1359,1384]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B7954FF98BDA57B5ACC3DFAB6" box="[916,1101,1359,1384]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">M. occidentalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of the truncate male tergite 8 projection, the bifid posterior lobe of the male cercus and the hypandrium without ventral setae. It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A89CA7954FF98BF787B89CA72FA6B" box="[329,514,1436,1461]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis id="B96E2E5B7954FF98BF787B89CA72FA6B" box="[329,514,1436,1461]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">M. occidentalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having a subrectangular apical protuberance on the hypandrium and well sclerotized ventral surface of the hypandrium.
</paragraph>
